SIMPLE: chaunter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chaunter
<hw>Chaunt"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A street
seller of ballads and other broadsides.</def> <mark>[Slang,
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A deceitful, tricky dealer or horse jockey.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was a horse <qex>chaunter</qex>; he's a leg now.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The flute of a bagpipe. See <er>Chanter</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chaunterie</ent>⟦br⟧
